text: They have the best employees ever! Every time I walk in, they already start pulling what I'm about to buy. And they are as nice as they can be. text: I went here to purchase some cigarettes for someone. I’m not a smoker. First, the business reeked of smoke as the person running the store was smoking inside the business. Save yourself some money and shop at Kroger or be aware that the so-called discount store charges more than most places probably.

name: Leonard Jarmon
text: I had a birthday party last night they treated me and my guest Great thanks for helping me have a great time

name: Lisa McCrory
text:
Love this place! Great selection of cigars. They have buy 10 get one free card that you get stamped. Great covered outdoor seating. It's BYOB so you don't have to pay for overpriced drinks and you are able to buy more cigars!
The Lesley and Robyn really go out of their way to take care of their guests. They have events with the top cigar makers all the time.

name: Joshua Waddell
text: Great people, very nice and friendly people, and a amazing atmosphere. The staff are very friendly and knowledgeable about cigars. I suggest that you go there for your tobacco needs!

name: John Jackson
text: Helpful and reasonably priced.

name: Tommy Woods
text: All the tobacco products you want right here

name: Juston Rideout
text: Great place and great customer service

name: Bobby Moore
text: I fear for beginners like myself. The owner shows zero personality or want to even have this business. I felt like I was not important or that my sales were not wanted. It sucks because this lounge is the only one in my area. I will make the commute to Decatur now. Beginners please know your pricing and sizes for there was an instense I was over changed on a simple transaction.

resp.text: If you were incorrectly charged for the wrong size, please let me know and we’d be glad to give you the correct size free of charge. We have 1,000s of cigars in our system and it may have been a mistake. We do apologize for any inconvenience. What cigar did you want to buy and what cigar were you charged for?

name: Billy Schofield
text: The best shop in town these days, Decent sized humidor and primarily focused on the good stuff, you wont find any trash sticks here. Great selection of pipes and tobacco. This place took a big turn for the best once a certain employee left... Humidor is ALWAYS in perfect condition, not sure what the other review is talking about... sounds like a hater and someone who knows nothing about cigars... Sounds like this John Randolph character is one of these drama queen cry baby grown men that doesn't know how to let stuff go... don't pay any attention to these reviews this place is great and has some awesome employees. This place isn't hurting for business at all. Its always been people hanging out and browsing the humidor every time Ive walked in the door and plus they have actual normal cigar lounge hours. Keep it up!!!

name: Trevor R
text: The Cigar Room is a top notch experience. A very welcoming atmosphere combined with the best selection of cigars, pipes,and tobbaco anywhere in the shoals. The staff is very knowledgeable and willing to help even if you're just learning or are already an aficionado they have something for you.

resp.text: Thank you for the kind words, Trevor. Come back anytime and see us.

name: Trey Edwards
text: Fantastic place with knowledgeable staff and awesome atmosphere. Left my five stars years ago but came back to post again after a negative experience somewhere else while on vacation that made me miss my old hangout. Hate that I haven't been able to visit The Cigar Room lately, and miss all the folks there. Married life in another town has kept me far too busy. Hope everyone there is well.

name: Lee Cornelius
text: Awwsome store with great people running it. They have anything you need for a great smoke.

resp.text: We appreciate you too, Lee! Thank you.

name: tee schenk
text: Friendly staff and they have a great selection of cigars and accessories.

resp.text: Thank you for the kind words. We appreciate your business. Come back and see us sometime.

name: Lee McClain
text: Josh was on the job with great customer service.  They have an awsome selection and nice atmosphere.   The outside area is very nice.

resp.text: Thanks for the kind words, Lee!

name: Hank Carter
text:
Great atmosphere and great staff.. special ordered my favorite cigars and arrived ahead of schedule...
Highly recommend this business

resp.text: Thank you, Hank! If you need anything else, just let us know.

name: Sea Dragon
text: Leslie is awesome! Had all the popular cigars! Refilled my torch! Comfortable relaxed lobby. The patio! Wow what a nice patio!

name: Robyn Russell
text: Great selection of fine cigars, wide variety of English and Aromatic pipe tobacco, tons of pipes, & great indoor/outdoor lounge. Discounts for all military with CAC Card, locker discounts, BYOB, monthly poker and games, great monthly rep/event nights. Great employees and customers!

name: B Cox
text: Great selection, great people.

name: Catherine Henry
text: Wonderful staff who are knowledgeable about their product. Friendly owner and we enjoy being able to hang out and just relax while smoking.

resp.text: Thank you, Cat. We love having you and John at the shop.

name: Steve Williams
text: Always helpful. Great selection and laid back atmosphere. Awesome

resp.text: Thank you, Steve.

name: John Randolph
text: I give them a three because just as the other shop in the Shoals have problems, this one does too. I have friends at both shops and I actually go to both, but they have some problems also. Their owner is a nice guy but doesn't realize sometimes that the customers should be trusted better. I am not saying that the customer is always right, because they are not. But neither are the managers or employees always right. We are human and we make mistakes. The owner just needs to own up to his mistakes and there might be more people coming to his shop.

name: Jeremy Porter
text: Brady, Gavin and Josh have an awesome selection of cigars waiting for you. Go in and they will guide you to whatever you want. Friendly, welcoming environment. Overall great place to go relax, and enjoy a great cigar.

name: Alabama Gemstones
text: Huge selection of stoges

name: Peggy Petrosky
text: Very helpful for novice cigar smokers. Enjoy a little relaxing cigar. They have a great selection.

name: W.C. Merrigan
text: The staff here are amazing, they're super helpful if you're new. The shop has a vast selection in every price range.

resp.text: Thank you!! If there’s anything you need and we don’t have, just let us know and we can try and get it.

name: Justin Dermody
text: Great outdoor patio area, friendly service, military programs and discounts, plus they carry my Drew Estate Acid Kuba Kuba cigars!

name: Maranda Fortenberry
text: The Family Dollar Store in Somerville.AL. is great. They usually have good weekly sales and great clearance items. The store is never cluttered and always clean. The employees are always friendly and helpful. I recommend going at night because they have a guy that works that shift that goes out of his way to help you and always makes sure to inform you of all sale and discounted items. He is just so helpful. Family Dollar should really pay attention to what a benefit he is for the company. I'm so sorry I can't remember his name at the moment but I will be posting it as soon as I can.

text: Love Somerville Family Dollar. Dewayne Holmes and Lynn were working they r so nice always friendly and helpful.

name: Wolfie Tv
text: Place is LARGE. Bigger than you think when u first walk in. At first you are greeted with a glass box filled with a plethora of different CIGARS. If your not sure of what CIGAR MOOD your in the host is happy to give recommendations. He RECOMMENDED me with Churchill’s last hour cigar after giving me a brief history lesson. His recommendation was right on the MONEY. If you choose to stick around a enjoy your cigar, behind the glass wonder box of cigar is a SPACIOUS LOUNGE where you and friends enjoy a pleasant even

resp.text: Thanks!

name: Jason Walsh
text: Had a really fun experience here, I learned about cigars, and Alabama. Bottom line was that the staff AND the patrons were all super friendly.  Feeling welcome at a place when you're from out of town is great. If your like cigars and bourbon stop by and find out for yourself!

name: Rebecca Dye
text:
Visited for the first time today, and loved it! Bigfoot was super helpful and gave my husband some sound advice on what to try. I explored the lounge in the back, which was quite handsome.

The entire store is masculine, sophisticated, and quite relaxing. It was pristinely clean, including the restrooms. I highly recommend coming in to shop and to spend some time.

We will be back, sooner rather than later.

resp.text: Thanks Rebecca!

name: Mike Williams
text: It is simply the best cigar lounge in the city.....

name: Melvin Ramsey
text: Real nice with their selections.

name: Amanda Atchenson
text: Very nice place. Good prices and a great variety of cigars. Very friendly staff also. The Arturo fuente double chateau is one of my favorites. It's a really good cigar if you prefer a milder cigar. The Arturo fuente king b is a great one also, it's a little stronger but not too bad.

name: LaShandra Hatcher
text: Staff is wonderful and the place is calm and welcoming. They have the best selection in town. Great place to unwind without drama unlike another establishment in town. Great location and close to everything Downtown!

resp.text: Thanks!!

text: A very nice place with excellent Cigar Selection and amazing customer service 😀!

resp.text: Thanks Oscar!

name: Marvin Wells
text: Perfection.

name: Paul Calhoun
text: What a fantastic place and a breath of fresh air.  The staff is knowledgeable but never pushy f,but never overbearing.  Smoking areas outside, upstairs, and downstairs with televisions everywhere. It's a great place to grab a cigar and watch a game.  A+ highly recommended.

name: Ted Danson
text: Wonderful place to enjoy a cigar or smoke my pipe.  They are friendly and helpful but not pushy.  Other places in town can't compare when it comes to the personnel vitola has brought in.  Top notch cigar selection with lots of seating areas.  Must try when in Tuscaloosa!!!!

name: Greg Wood
text: Had a good experience with John today around 12:30. I had a variety of needs. Pipe, torch, etc... he was very kind and patient with me and got set up real nice!!

Went in to buy a standard battery. The guy that helped me was nice and showed me a few batteries of different colors. This is why I gave even two stars instead of one. Decided on a color and payed.
This was a Thursday evening. This battery was for my mom who lives 2 hours away. So Friday night I give it to her and it doesn’t work whatsoever. The light doesn’t come on, no light to show battery is low- nothing. She charges it all night and on Saturday still nothing. On Sunday I call magic vape to let them know it never worked from the get go. He tells me he can’t give me my money back, which is ok but he wouldn’t even exchange it for one that did work. His reasoning was he couldn’t confirm I didn’t break it and was just trying to get another battery. He also said it could be the charger, after which I told him the charger worked fine.  He said if I would have returned it that night or the next morning, maybe. Which makes no sense. Wheather it was the next day or three days later. I assumed it would work since it was brand new out of the box. That’s just bad business. And I will NEVER shop there again. How can you not refund or AT LEAST just exchange a $10 battery that was broken right out of the box. So my mom goes to the vape shop in her hometown and buys an identical battery- and guess what...uses the same exact charger as she did on the first and this battery works great! She paid double but I’d rather pay double than use magic vape again!

text:
Wow. another place I haven't given a review for!!

Calera package store and I go way back.  Well, not really...but I popped into this location BEFORE I decided to move here.  We were scouting the area and I was intrigued by the idea of a wine boutique.  There was nothing like that available in Calera.  Shocker, right??  Any who, moving on....

Calera package store offers a variety of wines that you may or may not find in grocery stores. Today I bought two wines for my girl friend.  She walked in and they were sitting there waiting for her.  I recently bought a wine captain (not a fridge...totally different) and I need to fill it with wines that I can save and wine that I can drink. I bought one wine that she can keep for years and I bought another that she could save but lets be honest...she probably won't.
Good selection...great customer service and perfect for what I'm looking for to feed my  new found love of collecting wines!

name: Tony Canterberry
text:
Awesome place! My wife and I come here for all our tobacco needs. We first visited a few months ago, and met the owner, Bill, who is there nearly every day.

He stopped what he was doing to chat with us, learn our preferences, and show us items we may be interested in. Since then, Bill has become a friend, not just a shop owner.

Prices are a bit above average, but that's because Bill and his team take a great deal of time ensuring that every product meets their high standards of quality.

The selection is great. Pipes, vape juice, super-fresh RYO tobacco, rolling machines, and excellent cigars, even vintage memorabilia and lighters. If he doesn't have it, he'll order it for you. You can shop online, pay exorbitant shipping for stale products, or you can come here, and leave happy every time.

The cigar selection is amazing, and they just got a new humidor, and are likely stocking it as I type.

If you're a connoisseur of tobacco, and are looking for a local tobacconist who cares more about your satisfaction than the mighty dollar, this is the best place in town. If there was a 6-star rating, Bill and the fine folks at My Tobacco Shop would deserve it.

Only place I know near Alabaster to buy decent cigars.  The owner is extremely knowledgeable and helpful, they actually stayed open fifteen minutes late as I was caught in traffic and needed to pick up some sun growns for the weekend.

Can't say enough about their customer service. Always friendly with none of the typical attitude you get from other cigar sellers.

For a broad tobacco retailer it's amazing to experience someone that understands and is mindful to keep their humidors at the perfect conditions for a great smoke. I've never had a bad experience there.

Top tip: If you buy one of their Perdomo humipacks keep them sealed after using for keeping your small samples fresh.

This is one place I always support and hope others will as well.

text: I must be experiencing a different Family Dollar than those who are rating this store 5 stars.  I won't say all I have seen in there, but it is a very dirty, and unkempt store.  The current manager has to only be there for a paycheck.  When it first opened, the guy who ran that store would get rid of anyone who had nasty attitudes, and he kept that store clean and looking good.  This new manager, not a chance.  It is nothing to be making a purchase and the cashiers are on the phones arguing with their boyfriends.  There is another Family Dollar down the road and I will pass this one to instead shop at that one.  Family Dollar places these stores in mostly black neighborhoods, and does just enough, which is deplorable.  I should never go in a store where I am purchasing any foodstuffs and see rodents running across the floor.  Let me be clear however, there are one or two of the young ladies on staff there who do all they can to make this store better, but they are not manager, so they can only do so much.  I hate to be critical, but FD should be ashamed of themselves to allow these stores to be ran as such.

text: This is the closest family dollar store near my home and I can't even shop here because the debit machine is not working which it's been approximately two months now. This is a serious problem because most people use their debit cards and a lot of people are members of the smart spin club such as myself which you have to input your phone number in order to receive your coupons that you've clipped and some earned by free spins!!! By the machine being down this is not possible. I spend$50 plus dollars a week in Family Dollar and I want to use my coupons. This really is an outrage how corporate the district manager or whomever has let this problem linger so long. I spent almost$80 yesterday and the cashier was really sweet because she manually gave me the smart spin coupons but the rude store manager gets upset because it was a long line behind me. How about you get on the other register and take care of the guests because I wanted my coupons and she was only doing her job... The nerve of her. Take that anger and frustration out on corporate or whomever is responsible for taking care of this issue. You're already losing money don't due to something you can't control but don't lose more customers because of your terrible attitude. Overall I love family Dollar but this one is horrible 😢

name: Kenny Greg
text: I just recently, not even 15 mins, left the store to buy pipe tobacco. It’s a relatively cooler and rainy day here in Birmingham Al, with a hurricane coming this way, I decide to wear my hoodie to stay dry. I’ve walked into many different establishments before entering this one wearing my rain gear. Not one person disrespected me or treated me like I was insane for wearing things to keep the rain and cold off of me. When I finally entered the Standish meant, one of the persons within the store, was very helpful and considerate and help me find the products that I need. They treated me like a human and respected me. I thanked them for their help several times. When I went to check out was when everything changed. I was scolded for wearing a hoodie and not seeing a sign that says no hoodies by a gentleman and a blonde old lady. Granted if I had seen the sign, it would’ve told me right away what it truly means: No PoC. I wouldn’t have walked in and took my business elsewhere. This store is in a predominately PoC neighborhood and they band people from wearing hoodies, even on rainy days. That should tell you the type of people they dont want to enter their store, even though they are surrounded by nothing but PoC. I even went back inside and said how rude it is to treat people that way. I even bought stuff with my Navy Fed card, and they showed no respect, and talked down to me like I was a second rate citizen. I never been so humiliated for just trying to stay dry. Seriously I thought we got passed this when Trayvon Martin died but it’s Birmingham so I’m not surprised.

resp.text: Sorry you felt that way. Well if you come in to the shop you need to pull your hoody of your head. It’s for security purposes.

text:
This is a great shop! Friendly staff, good hours, great location & the best part? They have many e-liquids in stock that Eco-Smoke doesn't. Don't get me wrong, I started out using a e-cig from Eco Smoke, but once they changed the tank system on their 808 (like the Halo G6) I started using carts. The new tanks looked good, but were a pain to use & broke WAY too easily. I'd be lucky if I was able to get 1 days use before it started to leak. Add in the fact that Eco Smoke is always out of any oil I like to buy in the mg I need in the smaller bottle, but they ALWAYS have the larger one. I buy my 30ml online, cheaper that way.

Twickenham Vapor is closer to my house, carries the tanks that I like, the oil I love in the mg I need & more often than not, it's CHEAPER at TW than Eco Smoke. I love the guys at Eco Smoke, but TW is a smarter bet in my opinion. If you use an e-cig, go there!

name: Frank & Shamona parler
text:
Ripping teenagers off!
My 15 year old daughter decided to get her screen fixed on her own with her own money. She only had $80.00. The vape shop charged her $59.99 to repair her screen and it only took 30 minuets. He repaired her screen, but when she attempted to make a call. Her speaker or camera wasn’t working. My son went back up there to only receive the message that it would cost another $49.99 to repair. I called up there and asked him why would he take her money and not correctly fix her phone causing more problems than before. The man went on stating he didn’t break her speaker but the person prior to him who fixed her phone damaged her speaker and camera. Now prior to him fixing my daughters phone, my son fixed her screen 8months ago and everything worked fine. I relayed this information to him in hopes of him reopening her phone to find the problem. He again stated, he will not. It will cost another $49.99. I asked for the manager. He replied he’s the owner. I said so your not gonna do anything about not fixing my daughters phone correctly. He said no. Unless you pay $49.99, there’s nothing else I can do. I said sir, do you know you just crushed a 15 year old lil girls heart who tried to do the right thing on her own? As to what I thought, he gave No reply. I will never enter this store again!

resp.text: Dear customer, your daughter came with a broken screen and said she wants to fix, and that is what we did. We replaced her screen with a brand new screen. Like you mentioned and like we told you, someone already tried to fix the phone before and they cut off the camera wire. Therefore, its not working. The camera replacement is different from the screen replacement. Thank you.

name: Addie Grace
text: Great place to visit for all of your tobacco needs, vape/juices, mods, U,-Haul, and all sorts of interesting items. You would usually just run into your local convenient store for just your usual pack of cigs, but with this store, you'll catch yourself somehow checking out the hats, shirts, jewelry, and everything else in between. I have been a long time customer (approx. 6-8yrs) of the Discount Tobacco store and I must say the customer service/cashier whose name is Nicole is amazingly nice and respectful. When it was just her and Smokey running the store,  those times were great and service was always 5 Stars, most definitely than any other store within this county. With Smokey no longer working there, I just hope they keep Nicole there because it wouldn't be the same without either 1 of them. I see them both as the backbone of this business and the reason it's as successful as it is today. With all of that being said, I highly recommend this Tobacco store to anyone looking for great deals on products along with being treated respectfully as a customer.

name: Maximillian Martin
text: I was in the store today and I am not able to wear a mask because of my medical conditions. The State of Alabama has legal exemptions in place for those of us with those conditions. I was there with my wife and she was wearing one. The 2 cashiers, after I had been through the store, wanted me to wear one. I told them that I have medical conditions. They not only proceeded to tell me that they wouldn't even check me out but called police to get me to leave. Now, after police got there they decided to let my wife pay for what we got. My wife is black and both cashiers were also, but I'm not. After  seeing proof from a doctor,  they still refused to help me even though they asked me for it. After I walked out they eventually checked her out. Now I'm no expert on discrimination,  but they saw us walk in together and she put one on but I didn't and I would think that they would have been able to figure out why I didn't,  but they didn't even ask. And there have also been other people in the store without masks, including their workers because I've done it before and no one ever said a word to me, even one who was there today was working without one. Something sounds a little fishy about their actions

name: Mariodupree
text: I went to Cigars and More the day after purchasing my first pipe set from another cigar shop and I hate that I didn't go there first! I walked in just to poke around and see what was what (because I already had my pipe set remember) and I was immediately drawn in by the atmosphere, friendly staff and how patient he was with all of my questions. The gentleman behind the counter walked me thru a selection of starter pipes, what to look for when purchasing a pipe and what they offered for my future needs. In fact, he was so helpful and informative that after talking to him for a little while it dawned on me that I had been burned (no pun intended) by the shop where I made my initial purchase. It may have beeen textbook salesmanship, I don't know but I ended up buying a new pipe with accessories and he threw in a bag of tobacco of my choice and a cool little box to store it in for free. All of that, and I still came out much cheaper with a better quality pipe than I purchased just the day before. Not only was the staff friendly but the customers who were there, all of which the salesman new by name, drew me in and not only helped me pick out a good starter tobacco but showed me how to pack it correctly and gave me a bag or two of their own to try. I'm sold! Great atmosphere. Great staff and products. Great regular customers! Its Cigars and More for me from now on.

resp.text: Thanks Mario!

text: I went there to buy my first pipe and the guy there was extremely helpful. He didn't rush me at all or make me feel like I was wasting his time. Also, he answered all questions I had without trying to  make me feel like an idiot (We've all come across those people). He pointed things out in the shop that I might want to check out and didn't try to up sale me from the type of pipe I knew I wanted. There were a few regulars there. I know this because he knew all of them on a first name basis (That's how you treat customers). I really like this shop and plan on being back. I left with a new pipe, some tobacco, a pipe tool, a pipe cleaner, and he threw in a box to keep everything together... all for under $50 after tax. Yeah... I'll definitely be back.

name: Brent_ MiserWannaBe_3thousandX
text: Do not buy any Vaping hardware from this store. They will not Honor the manufacturer warranty. I bought a Smoke Novo here, the firing switch went out in just under 2 months. The Smok website instructs the buyer to return it for an exchange at the place of purchase if it is under 6 months old. Athens Smoke Shop refused to honor Smok's replacement program. Now I have to spend money on shipping and go without my pod system for a week. All Athens Smoke Shop had to do was make a call to have the unit replaced that they would of exchanged my faulty unit with. The other 2 main Vapor shops in Athens, Leet Vapors and Kick'n My Habit Vaps, honor the warranty. That's where I'll go for every Vap need for now on.
